For $n$ large, if $f(n) = o(n)$, then $\phi(n) - \phi(n - \phi(n))$ is expected to be of order $n$ (in fact, it's known that $\phi(n)$ is usually close to $n$ when $n$ is large, so $\phi(n) - \phi(n - \phi(n))$ could be as large as $O(n)$). So if $f(n) = o(n)$, then for large enough $n$, the inequality should hold.

