2. Then, the set of $n$ where the inequality holds is eventually true, and hence has density 1.

To prove step 1, we can use the fact that $\phi(n)$ is usually close to $n$ when $n$ is large, so $\phi(n) - \phi(n - \phi(n))$ is expected to be of order $n$, while $f(n) = o(n)$ is smaller. 

